"{\"uid\": \"nysun.com-article-as-olympic-idyll-recedes-french-fret-over-absentee-government-while-britain-grapples-with-more-migrants\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Summertime on the Continent and the crises just keep brewing.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 61, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the Olympic intoxication cometh le grand hangover: France still has no prime minister, and the new one in Britain appears to have missed the boat on what is actually ailing vast sections of British society: mismanagement of the migrant crisis.\", \"from\": 63, \"to\": 312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 120, \"end\": 126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9906070202629528, \"rank\": 0.009316936312619905, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999436522326316, \"rank\": 4.538570041106754e-05, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 259, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_society\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British society\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_society\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_society\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the background, war in Ukraine and a Middle East as muddled as ever.\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 339, \"end\": 346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999987337190591, \"rank\": 1.2624652996946083e-06, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris games gave the French a literal reprieve from the weeks of political turmoil that preceded them - or as Le Figaro put it, an \\\"insouciant parenthesis\\\" - but a new crisis is just around the corner.\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 390, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.766463270761926e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 411, \"end\": 417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8429472722785137, \"rank\": 0.18213875784125366, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the time of year when typically France powers down for summer vacation, but this year's mid-August break will be shorter than usual.\", \"from\": 592, \"to\": 732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9906070202629528, \"rank\": 0.009316936312619905, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Cruise came and went, the Olympics political \\\"truce\\\" that President Macron sought and received is over, and there is now mounting pressure on the \\u00c9lys\\u00e9e Palace to find a new prime minister by August 19.\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 733, \"end\": 743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 795, \"end\": 811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"President Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That does not leave much time.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A leading contender for the job is the New Popular Front's Lucie Castets, who currently works under the radical left-wing mayor ofParis, Anne Hidalgo, and recently came out as alesbian.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 1157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1015, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\", \"score\": 0.9992268376604639, \"rank\": 0.0007737605819531215, \"text\": \"Popular Front\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\"}, {\"begin\": 1037, \"end\": 1044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castets_(grape)\", \"score\": 0.5009607382045541, \"rank\": 0.6944444444443503, \"text\": \"Castets\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castets_(grape)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castets_(grape)\"}, {\"begin\": 1109, \"end\": 1121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Support from Mr. Macron is not assured.\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1175, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2908054375078968e-30, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The damage President Macron has done to the role of prime minister in recent years is substantial and it will take more than just a fresh face to energize the position.\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1210, \"end\": 1226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"President Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The caretaker prime minister, Gabriel Attal, handed in his resignation prior to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1399, \"end\": 1412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to French press reports, Mr. Attal\\u00a0 is no longer on speaking terms with Mr. Macron, although on Monday they jointly attend a reception at the \\u00c9lys\\u00e9e Palace to thank the Olympic organizers.\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1476, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French press\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_press\"}, {\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2908054375078968e-30, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With leading figures on the right such as the National Rally's Marine Le Pen and Jordan Bardella now more focused on solidifying their positions in the European Parliament, the French political theater's next act may avoid some of last spring's drama.\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1709, \"end\": 1723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}, {\"begin\": 1744, \"end\": 1759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Bardella\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Bardella\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Bardella\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Bardella\"}, {\"begin\": 1815, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Parliament\", \"score\": 0.9971789976615636, \"rank\": 0.002827246759115485, \"text\": \"European Parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Parliament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Parliament\"}, {\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8429472722785137, \"rank\": 0.18213875784125366, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France has an enduring supporting role in the turmoil that has roiled the British Isles in recent weeks.\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 2020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1916, \"end\": 1922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9906070202629528, \"rank\": 0.009316936312619905, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1990, \"end\": 2003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999992926089136, \"rank\": 5.501269815779987e-07, \"text\": \"British Isles\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The violent riots are over and the blame game has begun - it was all the fault of Elon Musk and that accursed social media, according to some policy cognoscenti in the Labor government - but the source of the trouble is still bubbling.\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2103, \"end\": 2112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}, {\"begin\": 2189, \"end\": 2194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 0.9999847472130574, \"rank\": 1.5253019535484629e-05, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the arrival on the English coast\\u00a0 of small boats, packed with migrants, that set off from the coast of France.\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2282, \"end\": 2289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"score\": 0.962300293853393, \"rank\": 0.03917228161667649, \"text\": \"English\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 2366, \"end\": 2372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9906070202629528, \"rank\": 0.009316936312619905, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Sunday a veritable flotilla of 11 such boats plied the English Channel, with data from the British Home Office indicating that more than 700 illegal migrants came ashore on that day.\", \"from\": 2375, \"to\": 2560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2477, \"end\": 2488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Home_Office\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.861656891340974e-30, \"text\": \"Home Office\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Home_Office\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Home_Office\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two migrants reportedly died trying to make the crossing, and some 50 were rescued from the water with what French authorities described as \\\"fuel burn injuries\\\" and were returned to France.\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2669, \"end\": 2675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8429472722785137, \"rank\": 0.18213875784125366, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2743, \"end\": 2749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9906070202629528, \"rank\": 0.009316936312619905, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the Home Office, the total number of arrivals to the United Kingdom in small boats in 2024 to date stands at a \\\"provisional\\\" 18,342.\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2769, \"end\": 2780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Home_Office\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.861656891340974e-30, \"text\": \"Home Office\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Home_Office\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Home_Office\"}, {\"begin\": 2818, \"end\": 2832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.984869457567116, \"rank\": 0.015362838613298837, \"text\": \"United Kingdom\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That figure is 13 percent higher than at the same point last year.\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On June 18 this year, 882 migrants crossed the Channel in a single day.\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 3036, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even before he was chosen as the new prime minister, Sir Keir Starmer repeatedly promised to \\\"smash the gangs\\\" operating in France and locations further afield that facilitate human smuggling.\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3091, \"end\": 3107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sir Keir Starmer\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\"}, {\"begin\": 3162, \"end\": 3168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9906070202629528, \"rank\": 0.009316936312619905, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So far, however, he has not done anything.\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has evoked the creation of a new \\\"Border Security Command\\\" that will give officers authority under 2008's Counter Terrorism Act to conduct stop-and-searches at the border, but it has not been created yet.\", \"from\": 3274, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Monday a spokesperson for 10 Downing Street said that \\\"summer is a challenging time\\\" for boat crossings and that \\\"we expect to see increases before we see improvements.\\\"\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3512, \"end\": 3529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/10_Downing_Street\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"10 Downing Street\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/10_Downing_Street\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/10_Downing_Street\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The government's inaction is already a liability, as the eruption of anti-immigrant riots in the wake of the murder of three young girls last month by the British son of Rwandan immigrants showed.\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3812, \"end\": 3819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999074823580785, \"rank\": 5.027586085696779e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New migrant arrivals, many of whom are asylum-seekers, are temporarily housed at hotels that are part of major brands like Holiday Inn Express.\", \"from\": 3855, \"to\": 3998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3978, \"end\": 3997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holiday_Inn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.570367819456057e-18, \"text\": \"Holiday Inn Express\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holiday_Inn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holiday_Inn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The system has gone haywire.\", \"from\": 4000, \"to\": 4028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Times of London first reported,immigrantsare now filling more new jobs than Britons.\", \"from\": 4029, \"to\": 4120, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That report follows Primer Minister Starmer's announcement last month that more than $85 million in aid will be allocated for African and Middle Eastern countries to try to address the migration crisis \\\"at its source.\\\"\", \"from\": 4122, \"to\": 4340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4260, \"end\": 4274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_East\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2883448511411127e-17, \"text\": \"Middle Eastern\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_East\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_East\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those schemes have not worked well for the European Union as a whole nor individual EU member countries like Italy.\", \"from\": 4342, \"to\": 4457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4394, \"end\": 4399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999993849375715, \"rank\": 6.054732171083422e-07, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4426, \"end\": 4428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.1443030541101223e-13, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 4451, \"end\": 4456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"score\": 0.9932057809439915, \"rank\": 0.006840695883413843, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The anger of the British working class is still palpable.\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4476, \"end\": 4483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999074823580785, \"rank\": 5.027586085696779e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No one excuses the recent violence, but the scent of outrage has yet to clear from many of Britain's economically flagging urban districts.\", \"from\": 4517, \"to\": 4656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4608, \"end\": 4615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999436522326316, \"rank\": 4.538570041106754e-05, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At least in France there were a couple of weeks of Olympic distraction.\", \"from\": 4658, \"to\": 4729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4670, \"end\": 4676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9906070202629528, \"rank\": 0.009316936312619905, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Britain, an absence of angry demonstrations today is no guarantee there will not be more looming around the corner.\", \"from\": 4730, \"to\": 4848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4733, \"end\": 4740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999436522326316, \"rank\": 4.538570041106754e-05, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr. Grant, a California native who has written for many major newspapers inclu